natural problem: Determine the value of $ab$ if $\log_8a+\log_4b^2=5$ and $\log_8b+\log_4a^2=7$.
natural solution: We add the two given equations, giving \[\begin{aligned} (\log_8 a + \log_4 b^2) + (\log_8 b + \log_4 a^2) &= 12 \\ \log_8 (ab) + \log_4 (a^2b^2)& = 12 \\ \log_8 p + \log_4 p^2 &= 12 \\ \log_8 p + 2 \log_4 p &= 12.

\end{aligned} \]Using the change-of-base formula, we have \[\log_8 p = \frac{\log_4 p}{\log_4 8} = \frac{\log_4 p}{3/2} = \frac{2}{3} \log_4 p,\]so we can write both logarithms in base $4$: \[ \tfrac{2}{3} \log_4 p + 2 \log_4 p = 12, \]or $\tfrac{8}{3} \log_4 p =12$.
